    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-04T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-04T09:00:00-05:00" n="1058"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1058">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94114 Supplies/218: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-04T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 4, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 4—2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1996. Department’s 1379, June 1, 7 p.m. Foreign Office states that it has no
                    objection to publication of the proposed press release on negotiations for shift
                    of supplies to Allied prisoners in Japan.<note n="95" xml:id="d1058fn1">The
                        statement released to the press on June 6 concerning the Japanese agreement
                        to pick up relief supplies and mail at a Soviet Pacific port for
                        distribution to Allied nationals interned in the Far East, with the
                        subsequent agreement to cooperate by the Soviet Union, is printed in
                        Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June 10, 1944, p.
                        536.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
